Optional(OEROptional optional, Class<T> type) {\n        return optional.getObject(type);\n    }\n\n    public static final class ReflectiveOptionalValue extends ASN1Object {\n        private static int invocationCount;\n        private static ASN1Encodable lastInput;\n        private final ASN1Encodable wrapped;\n\n        private ReflectiveOptionalValue(ASN1Encodable wrapped) {\n            this.wrapped = wrapped;\n        }\n\n        public static ReflectiveOptionalValue getInstance(Object value) {\n            invocationCount++;\n            lastInput = (ASN1Encodable) value;\n            return new ReflectiveOptionalValue(lastInput);\n        }\n\n        static void reset() {\n            invocationCount = 0;\n            lastInput = null;\n        }\n\n        static int getInvocationCount() {\n            return invocationCount;\n        }\n\n        static ASN1Encodable getLastInput() {\n            return lastInput;\n        }\n\n        ASN1Encodable getWrapped() {\n            return wrapped;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public ASN1Primitive toASN1Primitive() {\n            return wrapped.toASN1Primitive();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating testing approaches**\n\nIt seems Bouncycastle has a modular jar without debug but does provide the source. I’m considering adding the source to test dependencies, but I noticed Jacoco doesn’t use the source jar for line numbers, and the bytecode doesn’t contain them either. \n\nI thought about using a binary jar compiled from local sources, but that won't work. Since the user is asking again about the lack of coverage, I need to adapt to find a solution.\n\n**Refining test parameters**\n\nI'm thinking about avoiding using `$` in test class or file names, which seems acceptable. I want to refine OEROptionalAnonymous1Test to utilize observable custom targets instead of UINT8. I should consider testing the static methods, like getValue and getObject, but only on active call sites. Maybe the current test suffices, but since the dynamic engine can’t cover everything, the new test could demonstrate Method.invoke via side effects. I might need to import ASN1Encodable and use org.bouncycastle.asn1.DEROctetString and ASN1Primitive as well.\n\n**Analyzing test class functionality**\n\nI'm looking at the OEROptionalAnonymous1Test, particularly at the method that reflects on public instance retrieval. I see that the DEROctetString holds an encoded value. ReflectiveOptionalValue resets, and I need to ensure the object's wrapped value is the same as the encoded one while checking the invocation count. \n\nNow, I'm wondering about the static mutability in the test and if parallel execution is possible. I think Class#getMethod will correctly retrieve a public method of the nested static final class, and I might need to pass a derived type. However, I can't use direct reflection for tests due to constraints on dynamic class loading. I need an array for supported types without unnecessary complications.\n\n**Preventing constant folding**\n\nI'm thinking about pre