[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering testing coverage**\n\nI'm thinking about whether we should cover exception paths and instruction coverage lines. It seems like I could generate some test sources using Bouncy's OER encoding to work with real APIs. But I wonder if the dynamic coverage tool might only count calls under a native image run and not JaCoCo. The report indicates an issue, especially since the user mentioned no coverage. Adding a public API might be required, but perhaps I missed something with `value.getClass().isInstance(type)`.\n\n**Considering test strategies**\n\nI'm thinking about creating a local patched class using the same Fully Qualified Class Name (FQCN) just for test runtime and native compilation. This could help with line numbers and maintain the same behavior. However, I realize it violates the guideline of keeping tests outside the library's packages because the test source would be under `org/bouncycastle/oer/OEROptional.java`. Plus, it changes the library being tested, which is not ideal. So, that's a bit of a dilemma!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02bbd92d4b7f31a30169fbb680c60881a1b8d8a93e48ce460d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-7abQ5m14ZyOqHvVIA7jQYLuW1KJSlJN-aGaZdgQ_5fRGEJCxGtBoyAQPtGXonOwOfNcpG_9iTmd4SYdYPA6I4hMB6maPWL6PciLt6og7sqnzFgILzNvjxqFplSPXBZLXeKdmUry1EmMplyHQhrobXCnYFW4v0Q8ltHfJdRdD2lGLk9lrPE1KHC98D8J_kjD3SedaEJ6i9eKAaLplBrZw0WtsRM9QUcL5MORpxKrLSwzg44nFHIcrcO3074PcI5_U5lpdqoP3_4Nml98pDG2dUGEv36eAOWFdTAUtnp6JE-D2v5cnjOZRjYyKuNPo7RdtkaZwI_tCsCdH30l5XrlAZ194S4QWFVIxv5nTw6IsV4xArarU_ftkMP32F_3wsKwsh02oXEdb_Hw-t5obXtV-TZXekarFWa8Jxsnnf4CrzsmYwoG7Hpy9DfGdogbs-17o5PDAVf2IpBvKWINL_mzIbaJA4dJzAzFIAyAVNb2r3b0MZyOu8kU7rm5NI1e60PQ3a4EULLmYAjY52TrnTay6j0INbraQz5I3bsV9KrWFUsm0wfcdMHFscB9PlqXSnWHnZV4yGurLsCVA9XiEfkS5ZfwVY05b8dvYi4H75Rf9ay6X_cjldfMNI2R_XD4NhCgnl2-eU9LFvTnn51aKCaa-VkKaUzaH-UG-7b5LQI2MdluSCkBJaTOwNvGW33Eh0VAcc